SIMPLE: nuncupative
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nuncupative
<hw>Nun*cu"pa*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nuncupativus</ets> nominal: cf. F. <ets>nuncupatif</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Publicly or solemnly declaratory.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Nominal; existing only in name.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Oral; not written.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Nuncupative will</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>Nuncupative testament</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a will or testament
made by word of mouth only, before witnesses, as by a soldier or seaman,
and depending on oral testimony for proof.</cd>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj> </cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nuncupatory</ent>⟦br⟧
